<trans-unit id="tu3" xml:space="preserve">
<source xml:lang="en">In GIS, joins combine data from two tables based on a common field (non-spatial join) or based on location/geometry (spatial join).
Spatial joins link attributes based on geographic relationships (like intersection or proximity), while non-spatial joins rely on matching attribute values (like IDs).</source>
<target xml:lang="fr">In GIS, joins combine data from two tables based on a common field (non-spatial join) or based on location/geometry (spatial join).
Spatial joins link attributes based on geographic relationships (like intersection or proximity), while non-spatial joins rely on matching attribute values (like IDs).</target>
</trans-unit>
